The paper discusses the implementation of a knowledge engineering tool called BART that uses Bayesian reasoning and probabilistic techniques to build classificatory problem solvers. This fits naturally into the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The tool is also designed to manage uncertainty in systems, which could fall under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE). The paper also mentions the use of BART in managing intelligence reports, which could fall under the category of databases (cs.DB) or software engineering (cs.SE).
